   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   3 &amp; 1 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i(4 - 6) - \widehat j(12 + 2) + \widehat k( - 9 - 1)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {d_1} \times {d_2} =  - 2\widehat i - 14\widehat j - 10\widehat k$$<br><br>Now, <br><br>$$\left| {{d_1} \times {d_2}} \right| = \sqrt {{{( - 2)}^2} + {{( - 14)}^2} + {{( - 10)}^2}} $$<br><br>$$ = \sqrt {4 + 196 + 100}  = \sqrt {300} $$<br><br>$$ = 10\sqrt 3 $$<br><br>Hence, area of parallelogram <br><br>$$ = {1 \over 2} \times 10\sqrt 3  = 5\sqrt 3 $$ sq. units

